title: Associate Hole primitive with parent pcb_component_id
description: Associates Hole primitives with their parents pcb_component_id to ensure correct placement during auto-layout.
body:
This change ensures that Hole primitives are correctly associated with their parent's pcb_component_id during     
rendering.                                                                                                        

Previously, pcb_hole elements created from Hole primitives within a component's footprint were not linked to the  
parent PCB component. This caused them to be misplaced during auto-layout, as they were not treated as part of the
component.                                                                                                        

The fix resolves this by assigning the parent's pcb_component_id to the pcb_hole upon creation, which corrects the
behavior in the flashlight panel auto-layout test.

title: Emit solver:started event for Copper Pour pipeline execution
description: Adds a standardized solver:started event emission when the Copper Pour pipeline begins execution, including solver name, input parameters, and component name for improved observability.
body:
This PR adds a standardized `solver:started` event emission when the Copper Pour pipeline begins execution.
The event includes the solver name, full solver input parameters, and the originating component name.
`CopperPourPipelineSolver` is registered in the global solver registry for consistent identification.
New tests validate that the event is emitted with the expected structured payload.
An example test demonstrates end-to-end emission during circuit rendering.
This improves observability, debugging, and tooling integration around copper pour solving.

title: Add pinLabels prop to interconnect props
description: Adds an optional pinLabels property to InterconnectProps to allow labeling of pins like other components, ensuring runtime schema and TypeScript typings are in sync and documentation reflects the new prop.
body:
### Motivation
- Expose `pinLabels` on `interconnect` so pins can be labeled like other connectors/components (e.g. `connector`, `jumper`, `chip`).
- Keep the runtime schema and TypeScript typings in sync so parsing/validation accepts labeled pins.
- Ensure generated docs reflect the new prop so consumers see the change.

### Description
- Added an optional `pinLabels` property to `InterconnectProps` in `lib/components/interconnect.ts` and to the corresponding Zod schema using `schematicPinLabel`.
- Imported `schematicPinLabel` and `SchematicPinLabel` types and used a `record` schema matching other components (accepts numeric or label keys and single or array label values).
- Added a unit test `allows pinLabels` to `tests/interconnect.test.ts` to validate parsing of string and array pin labels.
- Regenerated documentation artifacts (`README.md`, `generated/COMPONENT_TYPES.md`, `generated/PROPS_OVERVIEW.md`) so docs include the new prop.

### Testing
- Ran `bun test tests/interconnect.test.ts` â€” all tests passed (5 passed, 0 failed).
- Ran TypeScript typecheck with `bunx tsc --noEmit` â€” completed successfully.
- Ran generation scripts and formatting: `bun scripts/generate-component-types.ts`, `bun scripts/generate-manual-edits-docs.ts`, `bun scripts/generate-readme-docs.ts`, `bun scripts/generate-props-overview.ts`, and `bun run format` â€” completed without errors.

title: Fix silkscreen rect PCB translation in footprints
description: Fixes incorrect positioning of silkscreen rectangles in footprints by using the global PCB transform instead of local offsets.
body:
### Motivation
- Silkscreen rect primitives inside footprints were using their local `pcbX`/`pcbY` resolution and not the full parent/global PCB transform.
- That caused silkscreen rects placed via a `<footprint>` (e.g. inside a `<chip>`) to not follow the chip's `pcbX`/`pcbY` offsets.
- The change ensures footprint primitives are positioned according to the composed/global PCB transform so they move with their parent component.

### Description
- Use the global transform position for silkscreen rects by replacing `getResolvedPcbPositionProp()` with `_getGlobalPcbPositionBeforeLayout()` in `lib/components/primitive-components/SilkscreenRect.ts`.
- Add a test `SilkscreenRect footprint positions respect chip pcbX/pcbY` in `tests/components/primitive-components/silkscreen-rect.test.tsx` that places a `<silkscreenrect>` inside a `<chip footprint>` and asserts the translated center coordinates.
- Minor formatting and committed the updated files.

### Testing
- Ran `BUN_UPDATE_SNAPSHOTS=1 bun test tests/components/primitive-components/silkscreen-rect.test.tsx` â€” 2 tests passed (the original rendering test and the new footprint position test).
- Ran `bunx tsc --noEmit` for type checking â€” succeeded.
- Ran `bun run format` â€” formatting completed successfully.

------
